node.text: Every day we wake up, we are given another opportunity and chance to be who we want and wish to be. I’ve spent the majority of my life growing in front of all of you… you’ve seen the good, the bad, and everything in between. Not only has my life been a journey for myself,  I was also living for those on the other side of the cameras. Today is a day I'm so happy to share more of my life with you all - I am proud to let you know that I identify as non-binary and will officially be changing my pronouns to they/them moving forward 💖 This has come after a lot of healing and self-reflective work. I’m still learning and coming into myself, and I don’t claim to be an expert or a spokesperson. Sharing this with you now opens another level of vulnerability for me. I’m doing this for those out there that haven’t been able to share who they truly are with their loved ones. Please keep living in your truths and know I am sending so much love your way xox

I voted NO in the CA Recall election because I care deeply about covid safety and women’s reproductive rights. But please do your research and vote!! Repost @WhenWeAllVote 

🚨CALIFORNIA! Your Governor is facing a recall election on September 14. Here’s what you need to know ⤵️⤵️

——

➡️ Governor Gavin Newsom is facing a Recall Election on September 14, 2021.

🗳 Recalls have been part of California’s political system since 1911; allowing the public to attempt to remove elected officials from office before the end of their terms. In order for a recall election to be initiated, a certain number of voters must sign a recall petition within a specified amount of time.

📋 There's just two questions on the ballot:

1️⃣ Question #1 "Shall Gavin Newsom be recalled from the Office of Governor?"

❌ A "no" vote keeps the Governor in office.

⭕️ A "yes" vote removes the Governor from office.

If more than 50% of people vote "no" on question 1 the governor will stay in office; If more than 50% of people vote "yes" he will be removed from office and replaced by whoever wins the most votes on Question 2.

2️⃣ Question #2 "Candidates to succeed Gavin Newsom as governor if he is recalled"

There are 46 candidates to choose from; Whoever has the most votes wins.

📣📣 If you want the current Governor to remain in office vote "no" on question #1 and either ignore question #2 or vote for the person you’d like to see replace him should the recall succeed.

📣📣 If you want the current Governor removed, vote “yes” on question #1 and vote for the person you’d like to see replace him should the recall succeed on question #2.

#CARecall #CaliforniaRecall #GavinNewsom

Today is the last day to register to vote to have your ballot mailed to you for the California Recall Election. You do not need to re-register unless you've changed your name or address. votesaveamerica.com/california

*If you miss the deadline today and need to register or update your registration, don't worry! You can register to vote the same day you cast your ballot up until 8 PM on September 14 at your county elections office, a vote center, or polling place.*
